Japanese and US officials are in talks to resume US beef shipments to Japan, the largest export market for US beef.
Japan had halted imports due to mad cow disease fears, but may now exempt younger cows from testing.
The disease, known as bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE), can be transmitted to humans, causing variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease (vCJD).
In Europe, embargoes on British beef may be lifted due to a decline in mad cow cases.
Meanwhile, countries like Bulgaria are using advanced testing methods to detect BSE.
